This article is a press gaggle with Press Secretary Josh Earnest during a trip on Air Force One. Earnest discusses various topics including President Obama's visit to South Carolina, the jobs report, the Ferguson report, the use of private email by Secretary Clinton, the offensive on Tikrit in Iraq, and the upcoming speech in Selma. Earnest also mentions the attack on the U.S. Ambassador to South Korea and the President's call with Ambassador Lippert. The article concludes with Earnest's comments on the importance of education and the Pell Grant program.